title: Grateful Dead Live at Madison Square Garden on 1988-09-24
lineage: Sony TC-D5M (original record deck) > Pre Sonus Inspire GT > Sound Forge > .wav files > Trader's Little Helper > flac files - matrix mixing by Kevin Tobin
description:
Set 1

Iko Iko, Feel Like A Stranger, West L.A. Fadeaway, Little Red Rooster, Box Of Rain, Ramble On Rose, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Don't Ease Me In

Set 2

Chinese Bones, Neighborhood Girls, Crazy Fingers, Women Are Smarter, Every Time You Go Away, What's Going On-> Drums-> Space-> The Wheel-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: Good Lovin', Knockin' On Heaven's Door

Show was a Rain Forrest Benefit, Other Artist(s): Mick Taylor on West LA and Rooster, Suzanne Vega on Chinese Bones, Neighborhood Girls and Heavan's Door, Daryl Hall and John Oats on Every Time and What's Going On, Baba Olatunji & Michael Hinton on Drums, Hornsby on NFA, Jack Cassady on both encores, Bruce Hornsby and the Range openned.

reviews.review_text: - Thanks for posting this: it's a very good quality tape. My rating is for the show. It's not very good. Very sloppy and lackluster. By no means the worst Dead show I ever heard, but a lot further from any of the good ones, all-star guest cast notwithstanding.

This is surprisingly good for a homemade matrix Oftentimes these mixes have phase problems. 

Here, the FM source is deficient enough by itself that the matrix actually elevates the listening experience. 

The show itself is what it is: a novelty/variety type of show with spotty performances, interesting and unusual guests onstage, kind of a weird way to end a long run at MSG, but still worth a spin on the hi-fi 30+ years later ...
